=== EDGE FUNCTIONS & DATABASE MIGRATIONS (MANDATORY) ===

Even without a Supabase project connected, you MUST create the correct files when the task requires them:

EDGE FUNCTIONS - create supabase/functions/<function-name>/index.ts for:
- LLM/AI features (chat, completions, embeddings, vector search)
- Third-party API integrations (Stripe, SendGrid, Twilio, OpenAI, Anthropic, etc.)
- Incoming webhooks from external services
- Any server-only logic or logic that must not expose secrets to the client
- Any prompt that says "create edge function" or "add edge function"
File location: supabase/functions/<function-name>/index.ts
Import pattern: import { serve } from "https://deno.land/std@0.168.0/http/server.ts";
Never expose API keys or secrets in client-side code.

DATABASE MIGRATIONS - create supabase/migrations/<YYYYMMDDHHmmss>_<description>.sql for:
- Every new database table, view, or enum mentioned in the task
- Every schema change (ALTER TABLE, new index, new policy, etc.)
- Any prompt that says "create migration" or describes a data model
Make migrations idempotent (IF NOT EXISTS / CREATE OR REPLACE). Include RLS policies.
Do NOT run "supabase db push" or execute SQL directly — only create the .sql files.

MANDATORY CHECKLIST - Before finishing, verify:
- [ ] Migration SQL file(s) created for every database table/schema change mentioned
- [ ] Edge Function file(s) created for every server-side/secrets feature mentioned
- [ ] TypeScript types created for every new database table

=== TASK ===
# Settings & Preferences

## Overview
Build a comprehensive Settings & Preferences module for PulseBoard, focused on User-level control over profile, team management, integrations, notification preferences, billing, data import/export utilities, and a gateway to the primary dashboard. This module also serves as the gateway for data import/export flows, OAuth-connected integrations (QuickBooks, Google Analytics, LinkedIn, Stripe, and CSV uploads), and internal CSV parsing utilities. All work must be wired to a cohesive design system, robust security, and runtime safety (null checks, safe array handling, proper state initialization). Ensure dependency-first implementation order: auth/access control and core data setup must precede dashboard/workspace/analytics tasks when both are present.

---

## Page Description (Full Detail)
What this page is:
- The Settings & Preferences page is the user-level hub for configuring personal identity, team capacity, integrations with external services, notification channels and preferences, billing access (with external payment provider link), and utilities for data export/import. It also exposes an internal CSV Import Utility (for parsing user-uploaded files) and acts as the control center for enabling and syncing data sources that feed into the Dashboard and Analytics workstreams.

Goals:
- Provide a single, cohesive interface for: profile management, team seats and invitations, integrations setup (OAuth credentials, permission scopes, and periodic syncs), notification settings (email and in-app), billing access/link to payments, and data import/export workflows (CSV import, CSV export, backups, and compliance exports).

Connected features:
- Data Import & Export: CSV import/export, data backups, compliance-ready exports, and integrations to bring in company data from external sources.
- Integrations & Connectors: Connectors to fetch financials and analytics from QuickBooks, Google Analytics, LinkedIn pages, Stripe, and CSV uploads. Handles OAuth flows, credential storage, and scheduled syncs.
- Notifications & Emails: Transactional and in-app notifications for completed analyses, export readiness, failed jobs, billing events, and admin alerts. Uses an email provider and an in-app inbox component.
- CSV Import Utility (Internal): Internal service to parse uploaded CSVs, validate and map to internal entities, and provide import previews.
- Dashboard (contextual navigation): Ensure settings changes reflect immediately in the user’s dashboard experience, especially around integrations, data sources, and notification preferences.

UI elements and how they need to look:
- Profile edit: fields for name, avatar, role, timezone, language, and preferred communication channel.
- Team management: invite flow (email, role), current members list, status indicators, and pending invites.
- Integrations center: OAuth connectors for QuickBooks, Google Analytics, LinkedIn, Stripe, and a simple CSV upload option; clear status indicators (connected, syncing, error); credential storage with encryption considerations.
- Notification preferences: toggles for email vs in-app, per-event notification controls (analyses completed, export ready, failed jobs, billing alerts, admin alerts), and inbox view for in-app messages.
- Billing: external link to payments provider; status indicator (subscription status, next billing date) and access to receipts.
- Data export/import: file upload for CSV import, import previews, mapping previews, and export buttons with selectable scopes (full backup, analytics data, financials, etc.).
- Danger zone: account deletion with confirmation prompt and data export reminder.

Visual guidance:
- Align with the PulseBoard design system: typography, spacing, color palette, and component styling. Use consistent card layouts, list groups, and form controls. Provide accessible UI with proper labels, focus states, and keyboard navigation.

API integrations:
- CSV Import Utility (Internal): Expose a service to parse user-uploaded CSVs, validate and map to internal entities, and return an import preview. Reference docs: https://example.internal/docs/csv-import

---

## Components to Build

1) SettingsContainer
- Purpose: orchestrates sub-sections, handles global save/apply actions, and state persistence.
- Props: userId, companyId context, initial settings payload.
- State: profile, team, integrations, notifications, billing, dataImport, dataExport, and danger state.
- Responsibilities: validate all sub-sections on save, trigger background syncs, reflect status changes in the dashboard.

2) ProfileEditor
- Fields: fullName, avatarUrl, jobTitle/role, timeZone, language.
- Validations: non-empty name, valid URL for avatar if provided, time zone in allowed set, language in supported locales.
- Behavior: image upload handling, optimistic UI updates, and local validation.

3) TeamManager
- Fields: addInviteEmail, roleSelector, currentMembers list with status pills.
- Features: invitation sending flow, pending state, removal request (with confirmation), role assignment future-proofing.
- Validations: email format, prevent self-invite, ensure capacity limits based on plan.

4) IntegrationsCenter
- Subcomponents for each connector:
  - QuickBooksConnector
  - GoogleAnalyticsConnector
  - LinkedInConnector
  - StripeConnector
  - CsvUploadConnector
- Each connector should support:
  - Connect button (OAuth flow initiation)
  - Status indicators (Not Connected, Connected, Syncing, Error)
  - Credential storage (secure, envelope with encryption strategy)
  - Permissions scopes display
  - Test/Sync now trigger
- Central OAuth credential vault: unify storage keys, encryption, and rotation strategy.

5) NotificationsCenter
- Toggles: emailEnabled, inAppEnabled, per-event toggles for:
  - analysisCompleted
  - exportReady
  - jobFailed
  - billingAlerts
  - adminAlerts
- In-app inbox: conversations/list of messages with read/unread status, reply capability for admins.

6) BillingPanel
- External payments link launcher
- Billing status summary: subscriptionState, planName, nextBillingDate, amountDue
- Receipts/history list with downloadable links
- Security: ensure tokens/keys never exposed in UI.

7) DataImportExportPanel
- ImportPanel
  - CSV file uploader
  - File validation (size, type)
  - Preview render (rows mapped, validation issues)
  - Mapping UI for fields to internal entities
  - Import job trigger and progress
- ExportPanel
  - Choose scope (full backup, analytics, financials, social data)
  - Export formats (CSV, JSON)
  - Download links or staged export emails
- Internal CSV Import Utility usage: call internal service to parse and preview.

8) DangerZone
- AccountDeletionModal with password/confirm, data export reminder, irreversible action.

9) DashboardLinkBridge (optional, for real-time sync status)
- Surface quick actions from Settings to Dashboard: re-sync, test connections, view latest sync status.

